# LMS Product Backlog

## Users & Groups

- [x] Support many-to-many relationships between tenant users and user groups
- [x] Support many-to-many relationships between clients and client groups
- [x] **Tenant:** CRUD APIs and admin UI for user groups and client groups
- [x] **Tenant:** Assign clients and tenant users to one or more groups
- [x] **Platform:** No group management needed (platform staff remain flat); document scope boundary

## Content Hierarchy

- [x] Define **Lesson** as the core learning unit, with types: text, file, video, and quiz
- [x] Allow lessons to be organized into groups and subgroups
- [x] Compose courses from lessons
- [x] Allow courses to exist standalone or as part of a programme
- [x] Compose programmes from courses
- [x] Mark individual courses within a programme as required or optional
- [x] Allow courses within a programme to be organized into groups and subgroups
- [x] **Tenant:** Add `Programme` model, APIs, and admin UI (course editor exists; programmes do not)
- [x] **Tenant:** Add lesson grouping (groups/subgroups) beyond flat `sortOrder`
- [x] **Tenant:** Add `QUIZ` to `LessonContentType` and wire quiz lesson playback
- [x] **Platform:** No content hierarchy management (tenant-scoped by design)

## Access, Pricing & Onboarding

- [x] Support free and paid pricing models for courses and programmes (paid-programme bundle checkout deferred to Fees & Payments; free self-enroll + staff onboarding done)
- [x] Add public and private visibility flags to courses and programmes
- [x] Allow clients to self-enroll only in public courses and programmes
- [x] Allow tenant users to manually onboard clients into private courses and programmes
- [x] **Tenant:** Add `isPublic` / `isPrivate` flags on `Course` (and `Programme` when built)
- [x] **Tenant:** Gate client catalog and self-enrollment APIs on public visibility
- [x] **Tenant:** Allow manual enrollment into private and paid offerings from admin
- [x] **Platform:** No learner onboarding (tenant responsibility)

## Fees & Payments

- [x] Build a fee module that can target an individual client or a client group
- [x] Allow tenant users to track and manage client payments against assigned fees
- [x] **Tenant:** Add `Fee` and `FeePayment` models with client / client-group targeting
- [x] **Tenant:** Admin UI to create fees, assign targets, and track payment status
- [x] **Tenant:** Course payment reporting dashboard (`CoursePayment` rows exist but no admin UI)
- [x] **Platform:** Subscription plan CRUD (plans are seed-only today)
- [x] **Platform:** Tenant billing lifecycle UI exists; extend for plan catalog management

## Assessments

- [x] Model quizzes as collections of questions
- [x] Build a question bank with multi-tag support and permissions scoped to users or user groups
- [x] **Tenant:** Add `Quiz`, `Question`, `QuestionBank`, and tag models
- [x] **Tenant:** Admin UI for question bank, quiz builder, and lesson-quiz linking
- [x] **Tenant:** Client quiz attempt and scoring flow
- [x] **Platform:** No assessment content (tenant-scoped by design)
- [x] **Note:** Assignments (`Assignment`, `Submission`, `Grade`) exist today as a separate free-form workflow (preserved unchanged)

## Certificates

- [x] Link certificate awards to course or programme completion
- [x] Build a WYSIWYG templating engine for certificate design and customization
- [x] **Tenant:** Add `Certificate` and `CertificateAward` models tied to course/programme completion
- [x] **Tenant:** WYSIWYG certificate template editor and PDF/image generation (live-preview editor; PDF via browser print/download — no new dependency)
- [x] **Tenant:** Client view/download for earned certificates
- [x] **Platform:** No certificate management (tenant-scoped by design)
- [x] **Note:** `Template` model exists with read-only admin list but no API or editor (`docs/gaps/10-template-management.md`) (Template CRUD now added)

## Calendar & Events

- [x] Build a calendar/events module for scheduling tenant activities (sessions, deadlines, announcements, etc.)
- [x] Allow events to target individual clients or client groups
- [x] Support event types (e.g. live session, deadline, reminder, general announcement)
- [x] **Tenant:** Add `Event` model with client / client-group targeting and recurrence options
- [x] **Tenant:** Admin UI to create, edit, and manage events on a calendar view
- [x] **Tenant:** Client calendar view showing events relevant to the logged-in client (direct or via group)
- [x] **Platform:** No calendar/events (tenant-scoped by design)
- [x] **Note:** `Assignment.dueAt` is the only scheduling field today; no calendar models or UI (calendar now added)

## Message Center & Notifications

- [x] Build an in-app message center for tenant-to-client communication
- [x] Build a notification system with in-app and email delivery channels
- [x] Allow messages and notifications to target individual clients or client groups
- [x] Support per-user notification preferences (in-app, email, per category)
- [x] **Tenant:** Add `Message`, `Notification`, and `NotificationPreference` models
- [x] **Tenant:** Admin UI to compose and send messages/notifications to clients or groups
- [x] **Tenant:** Client inbox and notification bell with read/unread tracking
- [x] **Tenant:** Wire transactional email (`lib/email/send.ts`) into the notification pipeline
- [ ] **Platform:** Platform-to-tenant announcements (optional future scope — intentionally deferred)
- [x] **Platform:** Email/OTP config remains env-based today; no notification UI (by design)
- [x] **Note:** Only transactional email (invites, OTP, password reset) and client-side toasts exist today (superseded by the messaging pipeline)

## Resources (File Management)

- [x] Build a resources module for centralized multimedia file management
- [x] Support multiple file types (images, documents, video, audio, etc.)
- [x] Allow multi-tag labeling and permission scoping on resources
- [x] Allow resources to be organized into groups and subgroups (folders/collections)
- [x] Allow resources to be linked/reused across lessons, courses, and other modules
- [x] **Tenant:** Add `Resource`, `ResourceTag`, and `ResourceGroup` models
- [x] **Tenant:** Admin file browser with upload, preview, tagging, and grouping
- [x] **Tenant:** Wire presigned upload routes for all `PresignKind` values (`logo`, `course_thumbnail`, `lesson_asset` — only logo is wired today)
- [x] **Tenant:** Enforce storage quota (`lib/storage/quota.ts`) on all upload paths, not just logo
- [x] **Tenant:** Replace manual `assetKey` / `thumbnailKey` entry in course editor with resource picker
- [x] **Tenant:** Add presign/upload flow for assignment file submissions (API accepts `fileKey` but no upload UI)
- [x] **Platform:** Storage quota and usage stats on tenant detail (exists); no file browser
- [x] **Note:** S3 infra (`lib/storage/s3.ts`), quota tracking, and reconcile job exist but are largely unwired (now wired)

## Cross-Cutting: Tracking & Management Gaps

### Tenant admin — missing or incomplete today

- [x] Programme management (model, API, UI)
- [x] User groups and client groups (model, API, UI)
- [x] Public/private visibility on courses and programmes
- [x] Fee module and payment tracking per client/group
- [x] Course payment reporting (`CoursePayment` has no admin list)
- [x] Quiz and question bank management
- [x] Certificate design and award tracking
- [x] Calendar and events with group targeting
- [x] Message center and notification preferences
- [x] Resource library with upload, tags, and grouping
- [x] Template CRUD (`/admin/templates` is read-only; no API)
- [x] Thumbnail and lesson asset upload UI (presign routes missing)
- [x] Assignment submission file upload UI

### Platform admin — missing or incomplete today

- [x] Subscription plan CRUD (plans seeded in `prisma/seed.ts` only)
- [ ] Platform-to-tenant announcement / broadcast channel (optional)
- [x] Cross-tenant analytics and reporting dashboard
- [x] Audit log viewer for platform and tenant actions
- [x] Document which features are intentionally tenant-scoped vs platform-scoped

### Client surface — missing or incomplete today

- [x] Programme catalog and enrollment (when programmes exist)
- [x] Quiz taking and results view
- [x] Certificate download
- [x] Calendar view for targeted events
- [x] Inbox and notification center
- [x] Resource access from linked lessons/courses
